race.comment: OHOPE (2) improving colt who sat off the fast tempo before swamping them late when a decisive winner of the LR The Tapp-Craig at Rosehill over 1400m. Even better placed out to the mile and maps to stalk the fast tempo. Tough to stop. RIVELLINO (1) talented colt struggling to recapture the good form he displayed in his two-year-old season. Drifted back and failed to make an impression when eighth in the G1 Caulfield Guineas over this trip. Comes back a few levels for this and reunites with Rawiller. Respect. RUINATION (4) speared across from the wide gate and dug in late when a gritty second in the LR Dulcify over this track and trip. Worth noting Berry hops off OHOPE to stick with this colt. DUKE OF ARRAKIS (8) raced too keenly with the blinkers when a fading last in the LR The Tapp-Craig. Key jockey change and can lift.
